import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='age', kde=False, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['age'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean Age: {:.2f}'.format(data['age'].mean()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of ages in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Age')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    ax = sns.boxplot(x=data["height"], color="skyblue")
    ax.axvline(data["height"].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Mean Height: {:.2f}'.format(data["height"].mean()))
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.title("What is the average height of people in the dataset?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Height")
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax = sns.countplot(x="name", data=data, palette="Set2")
    for p in ax.patches:
        ax.annotate('{:.0f}'.format(p.get_height()), (p.get_x()+0.3, p.get_height()+0.5))
    plt.title('What is the most common name in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
